    <text id="B0001T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jordan informs a congregation that they are to allow a group of freedmen to use
                    their church for services, and asks them to not interfere.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Messrs Ross C. Eakle<lb/>And all whom it may
                        concern<lb/>Mt. Sidney,<lb/>Augusta <abbr expan="County">Co</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <address><addrLine>Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen, and Abandoned Lands,</addrLine><addrLine>Office 4th Division, 9th Sub-District, Virignia</addrLine></address>
                        <date value="1868-05-16">May 16, 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>
                        <abbr expan="Gentlemen">Gent</abbr>
                    </salute>
                </opener>

                <p>You are respectfully requested to give to the <abbr expan="Reverend">Rev.</abbr>
                    Mr. King the use of the <abbr expan="Methodist Episcopal">M. E.</abbr> Church at
                    the above named point for religious services on Sunday May 17, 1868 at 3:30 P.M.</p>

                <p>It is earnestly hoped that no demonstrations will be made interfering with the
                    peace and good order of the neighborhood tomorrow.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="obedient">obd.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="servant">svt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed><abbr expan="John">Jno</abbr> W. Jordan<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant">Asa</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Commissioner">Coms</abbr> &amp;c</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
